            "alt": "scrying",
            "aonid": 689,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "name": "scrying",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Eyes Behind the Mask",
        "subtype": "ability",
        "text": "A creature wearing the mask and garb of a priest of Razmir that outranks the tithekeeper's mask and ribbon rank can spend an hour Interacting with the tithekeeper's mask to connect with it. The creature's mask becomes an invested item that allows them to see and hear as though peering through the tithekeeper's mask. The creature must use a 3-action activity envisioning the tithekeeper to activate the scrying effect, and the effect can be Dismissed. Multiple creatures can create connections to the tithekeeper's mask simultaneously, and a creature can have connections to multiple tithekeepers with just one mask. Each connection ends after a week but can be renewed at any time.",
        "traits": [
          {
            "alternate_link": {
              "alternate_type": "legacy",
              "aonid": 141,
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "type": "alternate_link"
            },
            "edition": "remastered",
            "game-id": "985f7af5ffe2d17740eff2a722a117c1",
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "name": "Scrying",
            "sources": [
              {
                "errata": {
                  "alt": "2.0",
                  "aonid": 216,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "2.0",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Player Core pg. 460",
                  "aonid": 216,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Player Core pg. 460",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Player Core",
                "page": 460,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "A scrying effect lets you see, hear, or otherwise get sensory information from a distance using a sensor or apparatus, rather than your own eyes and ears.",
            "type": "trait"
          }
        ],
        "type": "stat_block_section"
      },
